article.headline: Cornell 82, Clarkson 37
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. -- Ryan Wittman had 15 points and was one of 14 Cornell players to score, leading the Big Red to an 82-37 rout over Clarkson University on Monday night. Jeff Foote added 14 points and Louis Dale had 10 for the Big Red (14-3), who have won back-to-back games and 12 of their last 13. Foote grabbed eight rebounds while Wittman hit three 3-pointers and Dale knocked down two from long range. The Big Red opened the game on a 22-7 run, led by 18 at the break and put together a 23-3 run in the second half to seal the rout. Cornell shot 49.3 percent from the floor for the game (34-for-69) compared to just 25 percent (13-for-52) for Clarkson. The Golden Knights (6-4) didn't have a player in double figures, as Felix Llanos and Elson Pickering scored eight points apiece to lead Division III Clarkson.
